  "text": "CMR is being increasingly used as a standard tool in the evaluation of RV structure and function [CITATION_1] and it has become the state-of-the-art imaging technique for evaluating the consequences of infarction, not only on the LV 8,14 but also on the RV. [CITATION_2] In order to confirm the well-established repercussion of inferior infarctions on the RV by means of our CMR approach, we evaluated an additional series of 10 patients with a first inferior STEMI. CMR solidly demonstrated the extent of area at risk, salvaged, and infarcted myocardium in both ventricles (see Supplementary material online, Figure S4 and Table S2 ). This approach represents an interesting but so far unexplored tool for the understanding of RV involvement in the context of anterior STEMI; this constituted the main objective of our study in patients.",
